Algorithm: Bank System Using Linked List
Step 1: Define Structure (Node)
Create a structure (Node) to store:
name
id
amount
pointer to next node
Step 2: Initialize Head
Start with a head = NULL (empty list)
Step 3: Create Account (Insert Node)
Input user details (name, id, amount)
Create a new node
If head == NULL, assign new node to head
Else, traverse to last node and insert
Step 4: Display All Accounts
Start from head
Traverse until NULL
Print each user's details
Step 5: Deposit Money
Input account id
Search node with matching id
Add amount to balance
Step 6: Withdraw Money
Input account id
Search node
Check if balance is sufficient
Subtract amount
Step 7: Search Account
Input id
Traverse list
If found → display details
Else → show "Not found"
Step 8: Delete Account
Input id
Traverse list
Adjust links to remove node
